<div id="review_405725153" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/405725153" />
    <a title="BestChickLit.com" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12115057-bestchicklit-com"><img alt="BestChickLit.com" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396532516p2/12115057.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/405725153?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="BestChickLit.com" class="user" itemprop="url" name="BestChickLit.com" href="/user/show/12115057-bestchicklit-com">BestChickLit.com</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer405725153" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13199315214805313096">Promise Cove is an emotional story that has been cleverly crafted into an engaging and uplifting read. At the heart of the book lies a tale of a small family destroyed by the raging war in Iraq and a small town’s unwillingness to step up and help one of their own.<br/><br/>Jordan really is a smashing character, with McKeehan effortlessly portraying her simultaneously as a grieving widow with the world on her shoulders, a caring mother and an intelligent woman trying her best to emotionally move on. Jordan</span>
  <span id="freeText13199315214805313096" style="display:none">Promise Cove is an emotional story that has been cleverly crafted into an engaging and uplifting read. At the heart of the book lies a tale of a small family destroyed by the raging war in Iraq and a small town’s unwillingness to step up and help one of their own.<br /><br />Jordan really is a smashing character, with McKeehan effortlessly portraying her simultaneously as a grieving widow with the world on her shoulders, a caring mother and an intelligent woman trying her best to emotionally move on. Jordan carries the book along with guilt-ridden Nick; the rugged but damaged male lead. Sexual tension between the two hums from the pages and the development of Nick’s character makes Promise Cove hard to put down. Certain scenes involving Nick, Jordon’s daughter Hutton and the town’s people are the book’s pulling power, adding depth and a touch of reality to a great storyline. A brilliant and rewarding read. <br /><br />Reviewed by Charlotte Foreman on behalf of BestChickLit.com</span>
  <a data-text-id="13199315214805313096" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

